Polish[edit]

Etymology[edit]

From po- +‎ biec.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • IPA(key): /ˈpɔ.bjɛt͡s/
  • Audio(file)
  • Rhymes: -ɔbjɛt͡s
  • Syllabification: po‧biec

Verb[edit]

pobiec pf

  1. (intransitive) to run forward
  2. (intransitive, colloquial) to nip, to dash (make a quick journey)
  3. (intransitive, literary, of thoughts, glances, etc.) to turn, to wander
